1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,268
Mean-Variance Optimization tells you to build a single portfolio on

2
00:00:05,368 --> 00:00:10,395
the efficient frontier. But real investors — from retail traders

3
00:00:10,495 --> 00:00:15,443
to billionaires — don't behave this way. They mentally separate

4
00:00:15,543 --> 00:00:20,090
their money into accounts: a safety layer, a growth layer,

5
00:00:20,190 --> 00:00:26,259
a speculation layer. Behavioral Portfolio Theory formalizes this behavior and

6
00:00:26,359 --> 00:00:32,348
produces portfolio structures that look radically different from Markowitz —

7
00:00:32,448 --> 00:00:37,316
and in many ways, more rational given actual human psychology.

8
00:00:39,200 --> 00:00:44,474
Welcome to QuantiFire. Behavioral Portfolio Theory was developed by

9
00:00:44,574 --> 00:00:48,886
Shefrin and Statman in 2000. It extends Prospect Theory

10
00:00:48,986 --> 00:00:54,180
into a portfolio framework. Understanding it has two applications:

11
00:00:54,280 --> 00:00:59,635
avoiding its pitfalls in your own decision-making, and understanding

12
00:00:59,735 --> 00:01:04,609
why retail and institutional investors hold the positions they

13
00:01:04,709 --> 00:01:08,620
do — which generates the anomalies quants exploit.

14
00:01:08,666 --> 00:01:15,514
The mental accounting framework: people don't think of their entire

15
00:01:15,614 --> 00:01:21,944
wealth as one unified portfolio. They think in mental accounts

16
00:01:22,044 --> 00:01:29,204
— buckets with different purposes, risk tolerances, and time horizons.

17
00:01:29,304 --> 00:01:34,493
The safety layer: money you cannot afford to lose —

18
00:01:34,593 --> 00:01:40,715
70 to 80% of capital. Risk tolerance near zero. Instruments:

19
00:01:40,815 --> 00:01:47,456
cash, FDIC insured deposits, stablecoin yield on Aave. The income

20
00:01:47,556 --> 00:01:52,849
layer: steady return for reinvestment — 15 to 20% of

21
00:01:52,949 --> 00:02:00,834
capital. Instruments: stETH staking, liquid staking tokens, bonds. The growth

22
00:02:00,934 --> 00:02:06,953
layer: long-term wealth accumulation — 5 to 10% of capital.

23
00:02:07,053 --> 00:02:14,938
Instruments: ETH, BTC, blue-chip DeFi tokens. The speculation layer: get-rich

24
00:02:15,038 --> 00:02:20,124
potential, accept total loss — 1 to 5% of capital.

25
00:02:20,224 --> 00:02:27,694
Instruments: options, altcoins, high-APY DeFi farms, new protocol tokens.

26
00:02:30,733 --> 00:02:38,132
The behavioral portfolio framework maps naturally to DeFi allocation. Safety:

27
00:02:38,232 --> 00:02:41,930
USDC or USDT in Aave or Compound — 4 to

28
00:02:42,030 --> 00:02:48,260
5% APY, minimal smart contract risk. Income: stETH staking, rETH,

29
00:02:48,360 --> 00:02:53,032
liquid staking — 4 to 5% plus ETH price exposure.

30
00:02:53,132 --> 00:02:59,168
Growth: ETH, BTC, blue-chip DeFi governance tokens like UNI and

31
00:02:59,268 --> 00:03:06,862
AAVE — market-linked returns. Speculation: high-APY farms, new protocol tokens,

32
00:03:06,962 --> 00:03:12,900
structured DeFi products — accept full loss. This framework is

33
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:20,496
psychologically comfortable AND financially reasonable if the layers are sized

34
00:03:20,596 --> 00:03:26,242
correctly. The key rule: size the speculation layer to what

35
00:03:26,342 --> 00:03:31,891
you can afford to lose entirely. A speculative loss should

36
00:03:31,991 --> 00:03:37,929
not psychologically contaminate your growth and safety layers.

37
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:43,419
If you use mental accounting — and you do, everyone does

38
00:03:43,519 --> 00:03:48,987
— use it deliberately. Define your layers explicitly, size them based

39
00:03:49,087 --> 00:03:54,636
on objective financial needs, and set rules for each layer separately.

40
00:03:54,736 --> 00:04:00,608
Acknowledge that your speculative layer will likely return negative 100% —

41
00:04:00,708 --> 00:04:07,306
size it accordingly. The structure prevents a speculative loss from psychologically

42
00:04:07,406 --> 00:04:13,197
contaminating your growth and safety layers. Final episode of the season:

43
